Hey @AnshuTrivedi! I updated the original post the include all the steps. I realized that this is a bit more involved in that it requires touching multiple files, but each step is very simple (moving files or adding/deleting 1 line in a file). I would suggest you make a commit for each bullet point.

Let me know if you have any questions or need help.

issue.title: fixes Move mug2vec to embed module #502
issue.body:
<!--
Thanks for contributing a pull request! Please ensure you have taken a look at

-->

#### Reference Issues/PRs
fixes #502 
<!--
Example: Fixes #1234. See also #3456.
Please use keywords (e.g., Fixes) to create link to the issues or pull requests
you resolved, so that they will automatically be closed when your pull request
is merged. See https://github.com/blog/1506-closing-issues-via-pull-requests
-->


#### What does this implement/fix? Explain your changes.
Move mug2vec to embed module
1.   Move file /graspologic/pipeline/mug2vec.py to /graspologic/embed/
2.   Change from ..embed to .embed once file is moved in mug2vec.py
3.  Remove /graspologic/pipeline/ folder entirely
4.  Add mug2vec to imports in the /graspologic/embed/__init__.py file
5.  Change imports from the test file graspologic.pipeline to graspologic.embed in 
     graspologic/tests/pipeline/test_mug2vec.py
6.   Add the line .. autoclass:: mug2vec to the /graspologic/docs/reference/embed.rst under .. autoclass:: MultipleASE
7.   Remove /graspologic/docs/reference/pipeline.rst file
8.  Remove the line pipeline from /graspologic/docs/reference/index.rst
#### Any other comments?

body: @AnshuTrivedi Thanks so much for engaging, we really appreciate the effort you have put in to this, and hope you can continue to be a part of our community!
